200","1320":"1320","1265":"1265","about 1200":"about 1200","1208":"1208","Of, Boves, Somme, France":"Boves, Somme, Picardie, France","Guilliers, Morbihan, France, France":"Guilliers, Morbihan, Brittany, France","Beaumetz-lès-Loges, Pas-de-Calais, France":"Beaumetz-lès-Loges, Pas-de-Calais, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert De Beaumetz was born about 1227, in Boves, Somme, Picardie, France, his father, Gilles I de Beaumetz, was 58 and his mother, Agnès de Coucy, was 54. He married Mabille de Rohan about 1253, in Guilliers, Morbihan, Brittany, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1270, at the age of 44."},"et":{"Abt 1227–1270":"umbes 1227–1270","1200–1264":"1200–1264","1201–Female":"1201–Surnud","1203–1265":"1203–1265","1206–Male":"1206–Surnud","1208–1264":"1208–1264","1211–1267":"1211–1267","1227–1270":"1227–1270","–1266":"–1266","1231–1270":"1231–1270","1264–1320":"1264–1320","1170–1214":"1170–1214","1175–1214":"1175–1214","Abt 1227":"umbes 1227","1264":"1264","1231":"1231","1175":"1175","1270":"1270","1170":"1170","1206":"1206","1227":"1227","1214":"1214","1203":"1203","ABT 1253":"umbes 1253","1267":"1267","1201":"1201","1266":"1266","1211":"1211","1200":"1200","1320":"1320","1265":"1265","about 1200":"umbes 1200","1208":"1208","Of, Boves, Somme, France":"Boves, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Guilliers, Morbihan, France, France":"Guilliers, Morbihan, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","Beaumetz-lès-Loges, Pas-de-Calais, France":"Beaumetz-lès-Loges, Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1227–1270":"noin 1227–1270","1200–1264":"1200–1264","1201–Female":"1201–Kuollut","1203–1265":"1203–1265","1206–Male":"1206–Kuollut","1208–1264":"1208–1264","1211–1267":"1211–1267","1227–1270":"1227–1270","–1266":"–1266","1231–1270":"1231–1270","1264–1320":"1264–1320","1170–1214":"1170–1214","1175–1214":"1175–1214","Abt 1227":"noin 1227","1264":"1264","1231":"1231","1175":"1175","1270":"1270","1170":"1170","1206":"1206","1227":"1227","1214":"1214","1203":"1203","ABT 1253":"noin 1253","1267":"1267","1201":"1201","1266":"1266","1211":"1211","1200":"1200","1320":"1320","1265":"1265","about 1200":"noin 1200","1208":"1208","Of, Boves, Somme, France":"Boves, Somme, Picardie, Ranska","Guilliers, Morbihan, France, France":"Guilliers, Morbihan, Bretagne, Ranska